{
  "texts": [
    "Some see ChatGPT as the future of teaching, learning, and educational research, while others consider it a threat that could limit the analytical skills of teachers and students.",
    "Among its main educational advantages are the ability to extend teaching reach, allow access to a greater variety and quantity of online educational resources, and provide personalized and automated feedback in the learning process [20,21].",
    "Many of these advantages can materialize with adequate knowledge of the tool's use, highlighting the importance of formulating specific and relevant questions to obtain coherent responses.",
    "Additionally, the implementation of ChatGPT as an educational tool will involve changes in many teaching aspects, such as adapting current evaluation methods and fostering creativity and critical thinking in students to maximize its benefits instead of limiting its use [22].",
    "It can also reduce teachers' workload in evaluation and feedback tasks."
  ]
}